    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I write one line merely to thank you for your most clear chart of the Runts.— With respect to your very kind offer of Runts, I will hereafter write to you: if, as I imagine, you allude to the Victoria or Smyrna Runts, though <hi rend="doubleUnderline">extremely</hi> pretty, I do not think they differ in proportions &amp; that is my <hi rend="underline">sole</hi> object.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> There would be no end to my collection if I allowed myself to be influenced by beauty.—</p>
<p>Far from thinking that you treated me “cavalierly” at Anerly, I was struck by your kindness, as on all other occasions, considering what a weight of work you had on your shoulders—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>In Haste | Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.3 Smyrna] ‘m’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘y’</note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.4 object—] <hi rend="italic">full stop over comma</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

